  "texts": [
    "Reference [33] proposed the Parallel Deformable Convolutional Module (PDCM), which solved the problem of insufficient spatial information of high-level features of small traffic signs and enhanced the feature extraction capability.",
    "Based on the YOLOv5 framework, they introduced the Sub-Pixel Convolutional Attention Module (SCAM), which is based on an attention mechanism to mitigate the effects of the target scale distribution so as to better focus on scale-dependent information.",
    "The introduction of GSConv reduced the computational complexity of the proposed algorithm, making it more suitable for industrial applications.",
    "These advancements in object detection algorithms within the context of traffic scenes demonstrate the continuous evolution and adaptation of deep learning methods to address specific challenges and improve detection performance in various traffic scenarios.",
    "Pedestrian DetectionIn traffic scene perception, detecting pedestrians in front of vehicles plays a vital role in inferring pedestrians' walking intentions based on their approximate positions and motion trajectories."
